name: GOOGLE_SHEETS__SPREADSHEET_CREATE
description: Creates a new spreadsheet with specified properties and sheets

body.description: Request body parameters for creating a spreadsheet

locale.description: The locale of the spreadsheet in one of the following formats: an ISO 639-1 language code such as 'en', or an ISO 639-1 language code plus an ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code, such as 'en_US'

autoRecalc.description: The amount of time to wait before volatile functions are recalculated

timeZone.description: The time zone of the spreadsheet, in CLDR format such as 'America/New_York'

iterativeCalculationSettings.description: Settings to control how iterative calculations are performed

maxIterations.description: When iterative calculation is enabled and the results differ between attempts, the maximum number of times to recalculate

convergenceThreshold.description: When iterative calculation is enabled, the minimum change between iterative calculations for the calculation to converge

index.description: The index of the sheet within the spreadsheet

rowCount.description: The number of rows in the grid

columnCount.description: The number of columns in the grid

frozenRowCount.description: The number of rows that are frozen in the grid

frozenColumnCount.description: The number of columns that are frozen in the grid

hideGridlines.description: True if the gridlines are hidden

namedRangeId.description: The ID of the named range

name.description: The name of the named range

sheetId.description: The sheet this range is on

startRowIndex.description: The start row (inclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded

endRowIndex.description: The end row (exclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded

startColumnIndex.description: The start column (inclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded

endColumnIndex.description: The end column (exclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded

developerMetadata.description: Developer metadata associated with the spreadsheet

metadataId.description: The ID of the developer metadata

metadataKey.description: The key of the developer metadata

metadataValue.description: The value of the developer metadata

visibility.description: The visibility of the developer metadata

location.description: The location of the developer metadata

dataSources.description: Data sources associated with the spreadsheet

dataSourceId.description: The ID of the data source

spec.description: The specification of the data source

dataSourceId.description: The ID of the data source

hours.description: Hours of day in 24 hour format
Hours of day in 24 hour format

daysOfWeek.description: Days of the week to refresh

hours.description: Hours of day in 24 hour format

daysOfMonth.description: Days of the month to refresh

name: GOOGLE_SHEETS__VALUES_GET
description: Retrieves data from specified range in a spreadsheet

spreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet to retrieve data from

range.description: The A1 notation or R1C1 notation of the range to retrieve values from

majorDimension.description: The major dimension that results should use

valueRenderOption.description: How values should be rendered in the output

dateTimeRenderOption.description: How dates, times, and durations should be represented in the output

name: GOOGLE_SHEETS__VALUES_UPDATE
description: Sets values in a range of a spreadsheet. The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID, range, and a valueInputOption.

spreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet to update

range.description: The A1 notation of the values to update

valueInputOption.description: How the input data should be interpreted

includeValuesInResponse.description: Determines if the update response should include the values of the cells that were updated. By default, responses do not include the updated values. If the range to write was larger than the range actually written, the response includes all values in the requested range (excluding trailing empty rows and columns).

responseValueRenderOption.description: Determines how values in the response should be rendered. The default render option is FORMATTED_VALUE.

responseDateTimeRenderOption.description: Determines how dates, times, and durations in the response should be rendered. This is ignored if responseValueRenderOption is FORMATTED_VALUE. The default dateTime render option is SERIAL_NUMBER.

body.description: The request body contains an instance of ValueRange

range.description: The range the values cover, in A1 notation. For output, this range indicates the entire requested range, even though the values will exclude trailing rows and columns. When appending values, this field represents the range to search for a table, after which values will be appended.

majorDimension.description: Indicates which dimension an operation should apply to. ROWS: Operates on the rows of a sheet. COLUMNS: Operates on the columns of a sheet. DIMENSION_UNSPECIFIED: The default value, do not use.

oneOf.description: String value. To set a cell to an empty value, use an empty string.

values.description: The data that was read or to be written. This is an array of arrays, the outer array representing all the data and each inner array representing a major dimension. Each item in the inner array corresponds with one cell. For output, empty trailing rows and columns will not be included. For input, supported value types are: bool, string, and double. Null values will be skipped.

name: GOOGLE_SHEETS__VALUES_BATCH_UPDATE
description: Sets values in one or more ranges of a spreadsheet. The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID, a valueInputOption, and one or more ValueRanges.

spreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet to update

body.description: The request body contains data with the following structure

valueInputOption.description: How the input data should be interpreted

data.description: The new values to apply to the spreadsheet

range.description: The range the values cover, in A1 notation. For output, this range indicates the entire requested range, even though the values will exclude trailing rows and columns.

majorDimension.description: Indicates which dimension an operation should apply to. ROWS: Operates on the rows of a sheet. COLUMNS: Operates on the columns of a sheet. DIMENSION_UNSPECIFIED: The default value, do not use.

oneOf.description: String value. To set a cell to an empty value, use an empty string.

values.description: The data that was read or to be written. This is an array of arrays, the outer array representing all the data and each inner array representing a major dimension. Each item in the inner array corresponds with one cell. For output, empty trailing rows and columns will not be included. For input, supported value types are: bool, string, and double. Null values will be skipped.

includeValuesInResponse.description: Determines if the update response should include the values of the cells that were updated. By default, responses do not include the updated values. The updatedData field within each of the BatchUpdateValuesResponse.responses contains the updated values. If the range to write was larger than the range actually written, the response includes all values in the requested range (excluding trailing empty rows and columns).

responseValueRenderOption.description: Determines how values in the response should be rendered. The default render option is FORMATTED_VALUE.

responseDateTimeRenderOption.description: Determines how dates, times, and durations in the response should be rendered. This is ignored if responseValueRenderOption is FORMATTED_VALUE. The default dateTime render option is SERIAL_NUMBER.

name: GOOGLE_SHEETS__VALUES_APPEND
description: Appends values to a spreadsheet. The input range is used to search for existing data and find a 'table' within that range. Values will be appended to the next row of the table, starting from the first column of the table. The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID, range, and a valueInputOption. The valueInputOption only controls how the input data will be added to the sheet (column-wise or row-wise), it does not influence what cell the data starts being written to.

spreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet to update

range.description: The A1 notation of a range to search for a logical table of data. Values are appended after the last row of the table.

valueInputOption.description: How the input data should be interpreted. This only controls how the input data will be added to the sheet (column-wise or row-wise), it does not influence what cell the data starts being written to.

insertDataOption.description: How the input data should be inserted

includeValuesInResponse.description: Determines if the update response should include the values of the cells that were appended. By default, responses do not include the updated values.

responseValueRenderOption.description: Determines how values in the response should be rendered. The default render option is FORMATTED_VALUE.

responseDateTimeRenderOption.description: Determines how dates, times, and durations in the response should be rendered. This is ignored if responseValueRenderOption is FORMATTED_VALUE. The default dateTime render option is SERIAL_NUMBER.
